Subject: [PATCH] cicd-golden-pipeline: add Java/Maven + legacy-EOL remediation
 patterns
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lessons from adapting the pipeline to a Spring Boot 2.7 + Angular app:

- Add Java/Maven row to the non-Node adaptation table. Trivy parses
  pom.xml directly for vuln scanning; syft needs dependency:resolve
  to run first so the runtime tree is on disk.
- New subsection: "Multi-language projects (e.g. Spring Boot + Angular)"
  covering paired setup-java + setup-node, ordering of SBOM pre-resolve
  steps, and scope of each audit tool.
- New subsection: "Legacy / EOL frameworks with unfixable CVEs" with
  two remediation patterns — BOM property overrides for transitive
  patches that stay within the framework line, and scoped .trivyignore
  entries for CVEs only fixed in the next major. Each .trivyignore
  entry must carry CVE-ID + justification + removal condition.
- New Pitfall: "Env-vars override profile-based test config" —
  SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=test + SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL env var silently
  defeats H2.
- New Pitfall: "Findings visible only to desktop reviewers" — use
  \$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY to surface CVE tables + surefire failures to
  mobile reviewers without a log drill-down. Ordering matters: JSON
  evidence first, summary next, gate last.

update-actions-node-version: add actions/setup-java row

v5.2.0 / be666c2fcd27ec809703dec50e508c2fdc7f6654, verified against
the javasprang Golden Pipeline PR.
